A reflexive graph \mathcal {A} \equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
,\approx _{\mathcal {A}}, \mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 is given by a type 
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
 of vertices together with a family of types 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \approx _{\mathcal {A}}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
 \to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  \mathsf {Type} of edges and an assignment \mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}} : \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
